                    <lb n="6"/>εὐχήν <hi rend="superscript"><foreign xml:lang="cyp">L S</foreign></hi>
                </ab></div> 
            

            
            <div type="translation">
                <p>To Opaon Melanthius, Katagraphus (dedicates) a votive offering on behalf of his
                    son Katagraphus in the sixth year. </p></div>
            
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Opaon Melanthius is a local deity known only from inscriptions found in the village of Amargetii. The symbols at the end read ἔτει ἕκτῳ (Myres).</p></div>
            
            
